      • get

        public ArrayList<AccessPermission> get(String userId)
        Retrieves list of available folder permissions (both local and remote)
        Parameters:

        Returns:
        list available folders

      • createPermission

        public AccessPermission createPermission(String userId,
                                         AccessPermission accessPermission)
        Creates a new access permission record to enable read or write privileges for a folder. User initiating request must have write privileges for the folder
        Parameters:
        userId - unique identifier for user creating record
        accessPermission - details about access permissions to create
        Returns:
        access permission data transfer object with unique record identifier
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the accessPermission object is null
        PermissionException - if specified user does not have write privileges on specified folder.

      • createRemotePermission

        public AccessPermission createRemotePermission(String userId,
                                               AccessPermission accessPermission)
        Creates an access folder permission for a remote user
        Parameters:
        userId - unique identifier of user sharing the folder
        accessPermission - access details
        Returns:
        wrapper around the unique identifier for the remote permission created
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the partner record cannot be retrieved

        protected RemoteClientModel getOrCreateRemoteClient(String remoteUserId,

        Checks if there is an existing client for the specified userId and remote partner. Retrieves and returns if so, or creates a new record if not
        Parameters:

        remotePartner - remote partner
        Returns:
        client model stored in the database with specified user id and partner
